12 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Revocation, suspension, denial, termination, and nonrenewal of
13 licenses for hiring, recruiting, referring, or employing aliens not lawfully authorized to accept
14 employment. (1) On receipt of the notice of revocation or suspension of the license pursuant to 39-2-305, a
15 licensing authority shall implement the revocation or suspension of the license by:
16 (a) determining if the licensing authority has issued a license to the person whose name appears
17 on the notice;
18 (b) entering the revocation or suspension on the appropriate records;
19 (c) reporting the revocation or suspension as appropriate; and
20 (d) if required by law, demanding surrender of the revoked or suspended license.
21 (2) The order revoking or suspending the license and notice of revocation or suspension pursuant
22 to 39-2-305 must be processed by the licensing authority without an additional review or hearing involving the
23 licensing authority concerning revocation or suspension of the license.
24 (3) Notwithstanding the provisions of any other law setting terms of revocation, suspension, denial,
25 termination, or nonrenewal of a license, an order issued pursuant to 39-2-305 revoking a license or suspending
26 a license must be implemented by the licensing authority and continues until the time period provided in the
27 order expires.
